## Problem

The issues table has indexes on project_identifier, last_sync_at, status, beads_issue_id, deleted_from_huly — but NOT on vibe_task_id or vibe_status, despite frequent lookups by these columns.

### Current indexes (database.js lines 117-121):
```sql
CREATE INDEX idx_issues_project ON issues(project_identifier);
CREATE INDEX idx_issues_last_sync ON issues(last_sync_at);
CREATE INDEX idx_issues_status ON issues(status);
CREATE INDEX idx_issues_beads_id ON issues(beads_issue_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_issues_deleted_from_huly ON issues(deleted_from_huly);
```

### Missing:
- vibe_task_id (INTEGER column, line 97) — used for Vibe task lookups during sync
- vibe_status (TEXT column, line 106) — used for status comparison checks

Additionally, in temporal/workflows/project-sync.ts (lines 296-300), every sync cycle regex-parses ALL Vibe task descriptions to build a Huly ID lookup map. This could be avoided if the DB tracked the vibe_task_id to identifier mapping with an index.

## Fix

Add indexes in lib/database/migrations.js (new migration function):

```js
export function migrateVibeIndexes(db) {
  db.exec(`
    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_issues_vibe_task_id ON issues(vibe_task_id);
    CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_issues_vibe_status ON issues(vibe_status);
  `);
}
```

Call it from runAllMigrations().

